- Adding source_check option to Cache.cached to have it include the function's
    source code when forming the hash key to store along with the cached data.
  - See Issue #154 for more details

commit.message:
Fix DeprecationWarning due to invalid escape sequences

Fixes #158
Overlooked these two renames

Rename caching backends in order to not cause any name collisions

All caching backends are now named using a consistent naming scheme:
"<backend type>cache.py".

Fixes #162

Add the classmethod as example in documentation

Closes #164

Use os.replace instead of werkzeug's rename

On windows os.rename raises OSError if the dst file already exist.

Explicitily pass default_timeout to RedisCache from RedisSentinelCache

See issue #172 for more details.

commit.message:
refactor solution to maintain backwards compatibility and fix test

This change replaces the previous method of using the existing
make_cache_key attribute of the returned decorator since that method
required that a slight behavioral change to that method be introduced,
which technically breaks backwards compatibility

honour the use_request argument to the make_cache_key function

This is technically a breaking API change, although a very small one, it
will have to be decided if that's okay.

refactor cached decorator to make it consistent with memoized

library consumers can now set their own make_cache_key
attribute of the returned cache decorator, accomidating use cases such as
the one in Issue 71 without even needing to change the public API since
this attribute has been documented read/write for years.
Minor text fix
